At the moment, JIRA Service Desk is only allowed to configure Parent issue types as Request Type. 

It would be great to have Subtask to be able to be configured as Request type. This would mean that Subtask tickets would be shown in customer portals. And this would also mean that agents can add customers as participant in that subtask issue and it will be listed in "My Request" of the customer.

Currently, it is not possible to create issues in JSD enabled projects through the IssueManager because it does not take account of the new _Service Desk Customer - Portal Access_ security type, the same is true for all other security checks like comment, add attachments etc.  The [createIssueObject|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/latest/com/atlassian/jira/issue/IssueManager.html#createIssueObject(java.lang.String, java.util.Map)] method below fails with a _CreateException_, indicating (for create) that the user does not have the CREATE_ISSUE permission:
{code:java}
ComponentAccessor.getIssueManager().createIssueObject(anIssueObject.getReporterUser(), anIssueObject);
{code}

The workaround I have applied is to modify the Projects Permission Scheme to add the Role _Service Desk Customers_ for each related JIRA Permission thats required, and this works.  The user involved does not start counting toward the JIRA user count (primary attribute of a JSD Portal User), and issues can be created and updated.  But, there is then a scary error warning on the Service Desk admin screen:

!permission-scheme.png|thumbnail!

Two things:
1. API issue creation with portal users as the issue reporter should just work, it doesn't.
2. I'm not sure what ill effects there would be over the workaround of adding _Service Desk Customers_ role in the permission scheme, comments regarding scary warning above?

